Given an object d\in  D, since Ud = U^TKd, K must define an
  algebra structure on the object Ud, i.e. a map TUd\xrightarrow {\gamma }   Ud. The counit UFUd\xrightarrow {U\epsilon _d} Ud of the adjunction
  F\dashv  U is such an algebra. Indeed, the diagrams 




