 of that monad, where U^T is the
forgetful functor and F^T is the free algebra functor.

We have that U^TF^T = T by construction. To show the
  adjunction, it suffices to give a unit and
  counit satisfying the triangle
  identities. The unit is the unit of the monad; the counit
  F^TU^T\xrightarrow {\epsilon }1_{C^T} at an algebra Tx\xrightarrow {f} x should be an algebra
  homomorphism Tx\to  x; f suffices, as the following square
  commutes by definition of a T-algebra:




